.TH rev 1
.SH NAME
\*Lrev\*O \- Reverses the sequence of characters in a line
.SH SYNOPSIS 
.PP 
.sS
\*Lrev\*O
\*O[\*Vfile\*O
\&...]
.sE 
.SH DESCRIPTION
.iX "rev command"
.iX "characters" "reversing"
.PP 
The \*Lrev\*O command copies the named files to standard output,
reversing the order of characters in every line.
If no file is specified, standard input is accepted.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP 
The following input is reversed as follows:
.iS
% rev
123456789
987654321
"able was I ere I saw elba"
"able was I ere I saw elba"
\*L<Ctrl-d>\*O\c
.iE
.EQ
delim off
.EN
